In your own words, what is the difference between frontend and backend web development? If you were hired to work on backend programming for a web application, what kinds of operations would you be working on?

Front end is what the user can see when they land on a web browser, the look of the page. This includes colors, styles, buttons etc. Whereas the back end focuses on what the user cannot see. It is for storing and organising data, ensuring everything on the front end side functions and achieves its purpose. APIs, authorisation and authentication as well as wiring with databases would be the kinds of tasks that a backend developer would work on. 


